  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support the Healing Garden for Survivors of Trauma</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Healing Garden in Chamchamal, a town originally populated through forced resettlement in Kurdistan-Iraq, provides a unique space for survivors of trauma and persecution to engage in trauma therapy through a variety of programs. Built in response to local therapists, the garden offers occupational, horticultural, play, art and animal-assisted therapies. Locals may use its weaving loom, pottery kiln, and various agricultural products to earn their own living, essential for long-term recovery.</narrative>
  </description>
